	&#xB7;

</FONT>

<EFX_PART_I>
<A NAME="FIS_PART_I"></A>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	PART
</FONT>
<A NAME="ZYNC-20151231X10K_HTM_PARTI_206585">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	I
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<EFX_BUSINESS>
<A NAME="FIS_BUSINESS"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Item 1.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Busines
</FONT>
<A NAME="ZYNC-20151231X10K_HTM_ITEM1BUSINESS_295234">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	s
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Unless the context indicates otherwise, the terms &#x201C;Zynerba,&#x201D; &#x201C;Zynerba Pharmaceuticals,&#x201D; &#x201C;we,&#x201D; &#x201C;us,&#x201D; &#x201C;our,&#x201D; &#x201C;our company&#x201D; and &#x201C;our business&#x201D; refer to Zynerba Pharmaceuticals,&nbsp;Inc.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Company Overview
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We are a specialty pharmaceutical company focused on developing and commercializing proprietary next
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;generation synthetic cannabinoid therapeutics formulated for transdermal delivery. We are evaluating two patent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;protected product candidates, ZYN002 and ZYN001, in five indications. We intend to study ZYN002 in patients with refractory epilepsy, osteoarthritis
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	OA
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Fragile X syndrome
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	FXS. We intend to study ZYN001 in patients with fibromyalgia and peripheral neuropathic pain. We believe these product candidates will provide new treatment options for patients, as well as additional treatment options for patients not currently receiving adequate relief from current treatment regimens. We initiated Phase&nbsp;1 clinical trials for ZYN002 in October 2015 and expect to initiate Phase 2 clinical trials for ZYN002 in the second half of 2016. We expect to initiate Phase 1 clinical trials for ZYN001
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in the second half of 2016.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Cannabinoids are a class of compounds derived from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Cannabis
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	plants. The two primary cannabinoids contained in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Cannabis
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	are cannabidiol
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	CBD
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and &#x394;9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;tetrahydrocannabinol
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	THC. Clinical and preclinical data suggest that CBD has positive effects on treating refractory epilepsy, arthritis
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and FXS
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, and THC has positive effects on treating pain. In addition to ZYN002 and ZYN001 potentially offering first
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;line therapies to patients suffering from OA,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	FXS,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	fibromyalgia and peripheral neuropathic pain, we believe ZYN002 may provide a complementary treatment for patients suffering from epilepsy who are refractory to their current treatment regimens.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We believe that we offer an attractive alternative to existing cannabinoid therapies by synthetically manufacturing and transdermally delivering our product candidates. Most cannabinoid therapies have drawbacks and limitations due to their botanical (plant
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;derived) nature, as well as the fact that they are administered orally. Botanical cannabinoids create significant challenges for drug manufacturers because of the natural resources and security measures required to grow
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Cannabis
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, as well as the strict batch controls required by regulatory agencies in pharmaceutical manufacturing. In addition, we believe all currently approved and development
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;stage cannabinoid therapeutics, except ZYN002 and ZYN001, are designed to be administered orally which can lead to limitations in safety and efficacy including low bioavailability, inconsistent plasma levels, degradation by stomach acids, and significant first
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;pass liver metabolism. First
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;pass liver metabolism refers to the process by which the liver breaks down therapeutics ingested directly or indirectly through the gastrointestinal system, such as through oral or oral mucosal delivery methods, allowing only a small amount of drug to be absorbed into the circulatory system. In contrast, transdermal therapeutics are absorbed through the skin directly into the systemic circulation, avoiding first
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;pass liver metabolism and degradation by stomach acids, and potentially enabling lower dosage levels of active pharmaceutical ingredients and rapid and reliable absorption with high bioavailability, fewer negative psychoactive effects and fewer drug
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;drug interactions.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ZYN002 is the first and only synthetic CBD formulated as a permeation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;enhanced gel for transdermal delivery, and is patent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;protected through 2030. CBD is the primary non
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;psychoactive component of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Cannabis
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. In preclinical animal studies, ZYN002&#x2019;s permeation enhancer increased delivery of CBD through the layers of the skin and into the circulatory system. These preclinical studies suggest increased bioavailability, consistent plasma levels and the avoidance of first
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;pass liver metabolism. In addition, an
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	in vitro
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	study performed by us demonstrated that CBD is degraded to THC in an acidic environment such as the stomach. We believe such degradation may lead to increased psychoactive effects and may be avoided or minimized with the transdermal delivery of ZYN002, which maintains CBD in a neutral pH. ZYN002, which is being developed as a clear gel with once- or twice-daily dosing, is targeting treatment of refractory epilepsy, OA
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and FXS
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, which collectively affect millions of patients using treatments that currently comprise a multi
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;billion dollar market.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	W
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	e &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	have been granted
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	orphan drug designation from the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	U.S. Food and Drug Administration, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	FDA
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	for ZYN002 for the treatment of FXS
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ZYN001 is a pro
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;drug of THC that enables effective transdermal delivery via a patch and is patent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;protected through 2031. A pro
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;drug is a drug administered in an inactive or less active form and designed to enable more effective delivery, which is then converted into an active form through a normal metabolic process. In addition, we expect that ZYN001 will be classified by the FDA as a new chemical entity
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	NCE. In our preclinical animal studies, ZYN001 demonstrated effective skin permeation with sustained delivery and rapid conversion of ZYN001 to THC. These preclinical studies suggest increased bioavailability, consistent plasma levels and the avoidance of first
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;pass liver metabolism. In addition, preclinical
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	testing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	conducted
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	has
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	shown
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	no
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	genotoxicity findings
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage6"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#0563C1;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#ZYNC-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#0563C1;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	safety pharmacology findings consistent with those seen with THC
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. ZYN001 is targeting two pain indications
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	fibromyalgia and peripheral neuropathic pain.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In October 2015, we initiated a Phase 1 single rising dose clinical trial for ZYN002 in healthy human subjects (and in patients with refractory epilepsy) to evaluate the tolerability and pharmacokinetic, or PK, profile of ZYN002. Initial results from this trial indicate the ZYN002 was safe and well-tolerated at all tested dose levels. In January 2016, we initiated a Phase 1 multiple rising dose clinical trial for ZYN002 in healthy volunteers (and patients with epilepsy) to examine the tolerability, PK and pharmacodynamics, or PD, of multiple doses of ZYN002.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We plan to evaluate the tolerability and PK profile of ZYN001 in Phase 1 single rising dose clinical trials in healthy human subjects in the second half of 2016.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Subsequent to the single rising dose clinical trials, we intend to conduct Phase&nbsp;1 multiple rising dose clinical trials to examine the tolerability, PK and PD of multiple doses of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ZYN001
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in healthy human subjects and in patients with fibromyalgia. To complete the Phase&nbsp;1 program for both product candidates, we will conduct bioequivalence clinical trials assessing the PK when applied to various parts of the body (e.g.,&nbsp;arm, thigh and back).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Following the Phase 1 clinical trials, we
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	intend to initiate a Phase&nbsp;2a randomized, double
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;blind, placebo
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;controlled clinical trial comparing the efficacy and safety of multiple doses of ZYN002 to placebo in refractory epilepsy and OA. We intend to initiate an open label Phase&nbsp;2a clinical trial in FXS to evaluate efficacy and safety. We also intend to initiate a Phase&nbsp;2a randomized, double
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;blind, placebo
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;controlled clinical trial comparing the efficacy and safety of multiple doses of ZYN001 to placebo in fibromyalgia and peripheral neuropathic pain.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our key development programs and expected timelines for the development of ZYN002 and ZYN001 are shown in the table below:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT SOLID #000000 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Refractory&nbsp;Epilepsy
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="WIDTH:01.64%;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #CCEEFF;PADDING:0PT;">

</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT SOLID #000000 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Cannabinoid Science Overview
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Cannabinoids refer to a unique class of compounds derived from the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Cannabis
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	plant. Of the over 70&nbsp;cannabinoid compounds currently identified, THC and CBD are the primary cannabinoids used for pharmaceutical purposes. THC was identified as the major psychoactive cannabinoid and subsequently found to be a partial agonist of the CB
</FONT>
<SUB STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1
</SUB>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and CB
</FONT>
<SUB STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2
</SUB>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	receptors, activation of which stimulates the endogenous noradrenergic pathway, inducing antinociception and suggesting a role for THC in pain management.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	CBD, the main non
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;psychoactive component of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Cannabis
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, has little affinity for the CB
</FONT>
<SUB STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1
</SUB>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and CB
</FONT>
<SUB STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2
</SUB>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	receptors. It does, however, produce multiple effects, including blocking the equilibrative nucleoside transporter, the orphan G
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;protein
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;coupled receptor GRP55, and the transient receptor potential of melastatin type&nbsp;8 channel; enhancing activity of 5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;HT
</FONT>
<SUB STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1a
</SUB>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and glycine receptors and the transient receptor potential of ankyrin type&nbsp;1 channel; and regulating the intracellular effects of calcium. The influence of CBD on these targets&nbsp;&#x2014; each of which we believe plays a key role in neuronal excitability&nbsp;&#x2014; is the scientific basis for its antiepileptic potential.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	CBD inhibits
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the metabolism (breakdown) of two endocannabinoids (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	anandamide
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and 2-arachidonoylglycerol, or 2-AG)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. Inhibition of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the metabolism of these endocannabinoids
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	is thought to result in increased anandamide
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and 2-AG
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	availability and greater CB
</FONT>
<SUB STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1
</SUB>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and CB
</FONT>
<SUB STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2
</SUB>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	activation. Therefore, CBD acts as a facilitator of the endogenous endocannabinoid system, which modifies release of other neurotransmitters from presynaptic terminals. This modulation of neurotransmitter release from presynaptic neurons of various classes is the scientific basis for the use of CBD in the treatment of FXS.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	CBD exerts a range of anti
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;inflammatory effects, including attenuation of the endothelial cell activation, chemotaxis of inflammatory cells, suppression of T
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;cell macrophage reactivity, and induction of apoptosis of T cells, which suggests a possible therapeutic role in the treatment of OA. CBD&#x2019;s agonist effect on TRPV1 receptors leads to antihyperalgesia, which further suggests a possible role in the treatment of OA. Third
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;party studies suggest that psychotropic effects of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Cannabis
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	are caused by&nbsp;THC, not&nbsp;CBD.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>

	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Clinical and preclinical data suggest that THC has positive effects on treating pain and CBD has positive effects on treating epilepsy, arthritis
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and FXS
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. Clinical data suggest that THC and CBD have a very high therapeutic index. Interest in cannabinoid therapeutics has increased significantly over the past several years as preclinical and clinical data has emerged highlighting the potential efficacy and safety benefits of cannabinoid therapeutics. Dronabinol and nabilone, oral formulations of&nbsp;THC, have been approved by the&nbsp;FDA. In third
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;party studies, adverse events from oral THC including dronabinol and nabilone were primarily psychotropic and related to peak plasma levels. Many patients have received CBD
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;enriched
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Cannabis
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and Epidiolex
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:5PT;TOP:-4PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	&#xAE;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, a liquid formulation of highly concentrated CBD which is currently in development. The cannabinoid therapeutics market is expected to grow significantly due to the potential benefits these products may provide over existing therapies. For example, opioids are often the standard of care for treating various pain diseases but patients frequently experience adverse side effects, including addiction and opioid
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;induced constipation.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Our Product Candidates
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	ZYN002
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Overview
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ZYN002 is the first and only synthetic CBD formulated as a patent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;protected permeation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;enhanced gel for transdermal delivery (see Figure&nbsp;1).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Figure&nbsp;1&nbsp;&#x2014; Chemical structure and delivery of CBD.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2016/03/14/0001558370-16-004082_ZYNC20151231X10K001.JPG" STYLE="WIDTH: 6.3125IN; HEIGHT: 1.979167IN" ALT="PICTURE 2">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ZYN00
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2 is being developed as a clear
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	gel that is designed to provide consistent, controlled drug delivery with convenient once
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209; or twice
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;daily dosing. Because CBD is virtually insoluble in water, we use ethanol and propylene glycol as solubilizing agents and Transcutol
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:5PT;TOP:-4PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	&#xAE;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	HP as a permeation enhancer. All excipients in the gel have been classified as
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Generally Recognized As Safe, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	GRAS
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and have been used in transdermal products previously approved by the FDA.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The permeation enhancer in ZYN002 increases the delivery of CBD through the layers of the skin and into the circulatory system.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Transdermal delivery allows the CBD in ZYN002 to avoid stomach acid degradation and the first
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;pass liver metabolism that occurs with oral or oral mucosal delivery methods. Drugs applied transdermally are absorbed across the skin directly into the systemic circulation, enabling the potential to have rapid and reliable absorption with high bioavailability.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Market Overview
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	and Rationale
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We intend to study ZYN002 in the treatment of refractory epilepsy,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	OA
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	FXS
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Epilepsy&nbsp;&#x2014;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Epilepsy is a disease characterized by an enduring predisposition to generate epileptic seizures (transient symptoms due to abnormal neuronal activity in the brain) and by the neurobiological, cognitive, psychological, and social consequences of the condition. Partial seizures usually start in a small area of the temporal lobe or frontal lobe of the brain and quickly involve other areas of the brain that affect alertness and awareness. Partial seizures are the most common type of seizure, representing 35% of all epilepsies.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage8"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#0563C1;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#ZYNC-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#0563C1;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	According to Decision Resources, in 2012 there were approximately 2.2&nbsp;million epilepsy patients in the United States, and treatments for these patients represented a total U.S. market size of approximately $1.7&nbsp;billion.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We believe that ZYN002 may provide an effective treatment for refractory epilepsy based on the anticonvulsant effects of CBD due to its ability to reduce neuronal hyperexcitability shown in multiple
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	in vivo
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	models of epilepsy conducted by third parties. Epilepsy specialists and patient organizations have shown considerable interest in the potential therapeutic role of CBD in adults with epilepsy and, especially, children with intractable epilepsy. Two companies have active CBD development programs for the treatment of patients with Dravet&#x2019;s syndrome, or DS, or Lennox Gastaut syndrome, or LGS, both of which are rare and severe forms of pediatric epilepsy. Unlike these cannabinoid
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based epilepsy development programs, we are conducting development programs for ZYN002 in a much broader subset of the epilepsy population.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	No large
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;scale, placebo
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;controlled clinical trials of CBD for the treatment of patients with epilepsy (either pediatric or adult) have been published. However, in a small (fifteen patients), third
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;party Phase&nbsp;2 clinical trial, patients with a documented history of epilepsy were treated with crystalline CBD or placebo for up to 4.5&nbsp;months. A total of 88% of the CBD
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;treated group had a response to treatment, with 50% of patients experiencing considerable improvement and 38% reporting at least partial improvement. In a compassionate access study conducted by a third party, 162 patients with treatment resistant epilepsy were treated for at least 12 weeks with an oral CBD solution. In this open label study, 50% of patients with DS had a 50% reduction in seizures compared to baseline while 69% of patients with LGS had a 50% reduction in seizures compared to baseline. Our expected type of therapy is adjunctive, second-line therapy in patients with partial seizures with secondary generalization on a stable dose of an anticonvulsant with a history of failure.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Osteoarthritis&nbsp;&#x2014;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	OA is a degenerative joint disease that leads to wear and tear of the joints and affects the cartilage, joint lining, ligaments and bone. It is the most common form of joint disease and tends to occur most often in the hand joints, spine, hip, knees and great toes. It is characterized by the breakdown of the joint cartilage, bony changes in the joints and deterioration of the tendons and ligaments leading to pain and inflammation of the joint lining.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	According to Decision Resources, which defines OA as radiographically confirmed OA of any joint, in 2008 it was predicted that the total number of prevalent cases of OA would be approximately 129.5&nbsp;million by 2012. Treatment for patients suffering from OA represented a total U.S. market size of approximately $670.0&nbsp;million in 2012.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We believe that ZYN002 may provide an effective treatment for OA based on research we have conducted. We examined the efficacy of transdermal ZYN002 for reduction of inflammation and pain
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	in vivo
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, assessing adverse effects in a rat with complete Freund&#x2019;s adjuvant
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;induced monoarthritic knee. ZYN002 gel (0.6, 3.1, 6.2, or 62.3&nbsp;mg/day) was applied for four consecutive days after arthritis induction. The level of inflammation was assessed by knee joint circumference and immune cell invasion in histological sections.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Measurement of CBD plasma concentration revealed linearity with daily doses of 0.6 to 6.2&nbsp;mg of ZYN002. Compared with baseline, rats treated with ZYN002 gel had significant, dose
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;dependent reductions in knee joint and synovial membrane swelling, immune cell infiltration, and spontaneous pain rating scores (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	P
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x2264;0.05). Paw withdrawal latency, or PWL, recovered to near
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;baseline levels. Immunohistochemical analysis of spinal cord and dorsal root ganglia revealed dose
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;dependent reductions of pro
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;inflammatory biomarkers (CD11b/c, CGRP, TNF). The data suggests that topical ZYN002 has the potential to provide effective relief of pain and inflammation caused by OA.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our expected type of therapy is monotherapy, first-line therapy in patients with OA.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	FXS&nbsp;&#x2014;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	FXS is a genetic condition that causes intellectual disability, anxiety disorders, behavioral and learning challenges and various physical characteristics. The impairment can range from learning disabilities to more severe cognitive or intellectual disabilities. According to the National Fragile X Foundation, FXS affects 1 in 3,600 to 4,000 males and 1 in 4,000 to 6,000 females of all races and ethnic groups. Approximately 1 in 151 women carry the Fragile X gene and could pass it to their children. Approximately 1 in 468 men carry the Fragile X gene and their daughters will also be carriers. FXS is an autism spectrum disorder, and patients with FXS exhibit autism
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;like symptoms including cognitive impairment, anxiety and mood swings, attention deficit and heightened stimuli. Approximately 7% of women and 18% of men with FXS have seizures. People with FXS are affected throughout their lives. Currently, there are no known cures or approved therapies for the treatment of FXS. Special education and symptomatic treatments for anxiety and irritability are employed to lessen the burden of illness.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	FXS is the most common inherited intellectual disability. Based on the 2012 U.S. Census and FXS prevalence rates according to the National Fragile X Foundation, in 2012 there were approximately 71,000 patients with FXS in the United States.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We believe ZYN002 may provide an effective treatment for FXS based on its capacity to interact with the endocannabinoid system, which is compromised in patients with FXS. Specifically, CBD indirectly increases the concentration of the cannabinoids 2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;AG and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">

	&nbsp;

<A NAME="eolPage9"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#0563C1;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#ZYNC-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#0563C1;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	anandamide, which are endogenous ligands at the CB
</FONT>
<SUB STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1
</SUB>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and CB
</FONT>
<SUB STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2
</SUB>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	receptors. Furthermore, the Fragile
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	X mental retardation protein 1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	that is diminished in patients with FXS, is required for the production of 2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;AG. Therefore, FXS results in the reduction of endogenous stimulation of endocannabinoid receptors while CBD facilitates the availability of endogenous endocannabinoids, potentially attenuating the pathophysiology of the disease.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our expected type of therapy is monotherapy, first-line therapy in patients with FXS.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	In vitro and Preclinical Studies
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In an
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	in vitro
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	study, we evaluated the effects of exposing CBD to acidic conditions. We exposed CBD to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	simulated gastric fluid
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. Upon high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;performance liquid chromatography analysis of this solution, we found &#x394;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;8 THC and &#x394;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;9 THC compounds formed from the degradation of CBD in this acidic condition. These results suggest that CBD may degrade and form THC if delivered by oral or oral mucosal routes.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The PK of ZYN002 has been studied in three animal species: guinea pigs, Sprague
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;Dawley, or SD, rats and squirrel monkeys. PK refers to a drug&#x2019;s absorption, distribution, metabolism, and excretion from the body and measures, among other things, the concentration of the drug in the plasma. Based upon preclinical studies, the transdermal route of administration of ZYN002 achieves sustained, consistent CBD plasma levels.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Clinical Trials
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We have completed an extensive review of the literature related to preclinical toxicology of CBD and completed a mutagenicity study with ZYN002. This preclinical toxicology analysis was provided to the FDA for a pre
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209; Investigational New Drug, or IND, meeting held in the first quarter of 2015 and, the FDA confirmed that no further preclinical work would be required prior to the initiation of the Phase&nbsp;1 clinical program. We initiated Phase&nbsp;1 clinical trials in Australia in October 2015, and we expect to initiate Phase&nbsp;2 clinical trials in each indication in the second half of 2016. We
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	have
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	initiated a standard toxicology program for ZYN002 concurrently with the clinical program. The toxicology program will consist of standard single
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;dose toxicology, multiple
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;dose toxicology, reproductive studies and carcinogenicity studies.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Phase&nbsp;1 Clinical Trials&#x2014;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In October 2015, we initiated a Phase 1 single rising dose clinical trial of ZYN002.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Phase 1 study was a randomized, double-blind, placebo-controlled, clinical trial to assess the safety and pharmacokinetics of ZYN002 in 32 healthy volunteers and 12 patients with epilepsy. Initial results from the 32 healthy volunteers demonstrated that ZYN002 was safe and well tolerated at all four dose levels. There were no serious adverse events, no drug-related changes in ECGs or clinical laboratory values, and there were no discontinuations due to adverse events.&nbsp;&nbsp;Overall, the incidence of adverse events associated with ZYN002 was similar to placebo.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, ZYN002 demonstrated no impairment in the trail making test, a neuropsychological test of visual attention and task switching, which detects several cognitive impairments. Final results, including results from patients with epilepsy, are expected in the first half of 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In January 2016 we initiated a second Phase 1 clinical trial for ZYN002. The randomized, double-blind, placebo controlled trial, titled the &#x201C;Multiple Rising Dose Study in Healthy Volunteers and Patients with Epilepsy,&#x201D; will evaluate the PK profile and tolerability of ZYN002 in 24 healthy volunteers, followed by 12 patients with epilepsy. Results are expected in the first half of 2016.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	To complete the Phase&nbsp;1 program, we will conduct a bioequivalence clinical trial assessing the PK of ZYN002 when applied to various parts of the body (e.g.,&nbsp;arm, thigh and back).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	Indication
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="WIDTH:02.36%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #AUTO;PADDING:0PT;">

	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="WIDTH:16.66%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT SOLID #000000 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #AUTO;PADDING:0PT;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0.05PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 8PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	Patient&nbsp;Population
</FONT>

<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="WIDTH:02.36%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #CCEEFF;PADDING:0PT;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0.05PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="WIDTH:19.52%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #CCEEFF;PADDING:0PT;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0.05PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Open
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CAMBRIA MATH;">
	&#x2011;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	label trial to evaluate the efficacy and safety of ZYN002
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="WIDTH:01.24%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #CCEEFF;PADDING:0PT;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0.05PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT SOLID #000000 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Phase&nbsp;2b Clinical Trials
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#x2014; &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Depending on the results of Phase&nbsp;2a clinical trials, we may need to further define the dosing in Phase&nbsp;2b trials or we may proceed directly into Phase&nbsp;3 clinical trials.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Phase&nbsp;3 Clinical Trials
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#x2014; &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We intend to use the data from the Phase&nbsp;2 clinical trials outlined above to select doses of ZYN002 for our Phase&nbsp;3 program, which will consist of two randomized, double
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;blind, placebo
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;controlled clinical trials for each indication and open
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;label long
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;term clinical trials.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	ZYN001
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Overview
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ZYN001 is a pro-drug of THC that enables effective transdermal delivery via a patch and is patent protected through 2031. We expect that ZYN001 will be classified by the FDA as an NCE. The structure of the skin effectively inhibit the transdermal delivery of most therapeutics. Drugs classified as hydrophobic, such as THC, add an additional impediment to their transdermal delivery through the skin. THC is naturally hydrophobic and thus is unable to be effectively delivered through human skin.&nbsp;&nbsp;A pro
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;drug is a drug administered in an inactive or less active form and designed to enable more effective delivery, and then converted into an active form through a normal metabolic process. Chemically, ZYN001 is the synthetic D
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;glyceric acid ester of THC. Unlike THC, ZYN001 is able to be efficiently absorbed into the skin through transdermal delivery. After crossing the stratum corneum, ZYN001 is hydrolyzed back to THC and glyceric acid under physiological conditions, mainly due to the action of common enzymes in the skin tissue known as &#x201C;esterases.&#x201D; See Figure&nbsp;2 below.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	10
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage11"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#0563C1;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#ZYNC-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#0563C1;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Figure&nbsp;2. Hydrolysis of ZYN001 into glyceric acid and THC.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2016/03/14/0001558370-16-004082_ZYNC20151231X10K002.JPG" STYLE="WIDTH: 5.805555IN; HEIGHT: 1.472222IN" ALT="PICTURE 11">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The transdermal patch is a non-invasive, non-oral dosage form that has been proven to be an effective method of delivery in other U.S. Food and Drug Administration, or FDA, approved products. The ZYN001 transdermal patch contains a 4% ZYN001 gel formulation. We intend to test the ZYN001 patch for application to the arm, back and thigh. The drug substance is produced synthetically and is not derived or extracted from botanicals. The excipients in the patch have been classified as GRAS, and have been used in transdermal products previously approved by the FDA.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	As illustrated below in Figure&nbsp;3, transdermal delivery often provides more consistent plasma levels without the peaks and valleys often associated with an oral dosage form.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Figure&nbsp;3. Illustration of transdermal delivery.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2016/03/14/0001558370-16-004082_ZYNC20151231X10K003.JPG" STYLE="WIDTH: 4.069445IN; HEIGHT: 2.430556IN" ALT="PICTURE 6">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Market Overview and Rationale
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We intend to study ZYN001 for the treatment of fibromyalgia and peripheral neuropathic pain.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Fibromyalgia&nbsp;&#x2014;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Fibromyalgia is a chronic health problem that causes pain throughout the body and other symptoms such as fatigue and cognitive (memory or thought) problems.&nbsp;&nbsp;According to Decision Resources, in 2012, there were approximately 5.6&nbsp;million adult fibromyalgia patients in the United States, and pain treatment for these patients represented a total U.S. market size of approximately $1.6&nbsp;billion.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We believe that ZYN001 may provide an effective treatment for fibromyalgia based on the hypothesis that an endocannabinoid deficiency is the underlying cause of fibromyalgia, which may enable patients to benefit from therapy with an exogenous cannabinoid. Nabilone, a compound which is chemically similar but not identical to THC, has shown significant reduction in fibromyalgia pain in a third
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;party randomized clinical trial, but it has also been associated with dose limiting psychoactive adverse effects. We believe ZYN001 has the potential to treat fibromyalgia by delivering sustained, consistent plasma levels of THC to provide a therapeutic benefit with minimal psychoactive adverse effects. Our expected type of therapy is monotherapy, first-line therapy in patients with fibromyalgia.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	11
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage12"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#0563C1;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#ZYNC-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#0563C1;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Peripheral Neuropathic Pain&nbsp;&#x2014;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Neuropathic pain is defined as pain initiated or caused by a primary lesion or dysfunction of the central or peripheral nervous systems. In patients with peripheral neuropathic pain, the pain is a symptom of another disease that has caused nerve damage&nbsp;&#x2014; such as a herniated disc (lower back pain), diabetes (diabetic neuropathy), cancer (neuropathic cancer pain), or herpes zoster infection (postherpetic neuralgia)&nbsp;&#x2014; but it is recognized as a clinical condition on its own. Because the damage does not involve the brain or spinal cord, the resulting neuropathic pain is defined as peripheral.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	According to Decision Resources, in 2012 there were approximately 14.0&nbsp;million peripheral neuropathic pain patients in the United States, and pain treatment for these patients represented a total U.S. market size of approximately $4.0&nbsp;billion in 2012.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We believe that ZYN001 may provide effective treatment for peripheral neuropathic pain based on third
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;party studies in animals that have shown that cannabinoid receptors are found in high concentrations in the central nervous system, as well as on peripheral neurons and along the principal nociceptive pathways. The results of a third
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;party randomized, placebo
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;controlled clinical trial demonstrated that low
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;dose vaporized
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Cannabis
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	may reduce neuropathic pain which we believe suggests a role for THC in peripheral neuropathic pain management. Our expected type of therapy is monotherapy, first-line therapy in patients with peripheral neuropathic pain.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Preclinical Studies
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In preclinical studies, the transdermal route of administration of ZYN001 achieved consistent THC plasma levels that we believe will deliver therapeutic benefit with minimal psychoactive side effects thereby distinguishing it from oral and oral mucosal delivery systems.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	In vivo guinea pig PK&nbsp;&#x2014;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The PK of a 4% ZYN001 patch was examined in a hairless guinea pig model by adhering two patches, with a total of 6.25 cm
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:5PT;TOP:-4PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	active area, to the guinea pig. PK refers to a drug&#x2019;s absorption, distribution, metabolism, and excretion from the body and measures, among other things, the concentration of the drug in the plasma. The patches remained on the guinea pig for 72&nbsp;hours, and blood samples were obtained for 103&nbsp;hours. Plasma samples were analyzed by liquid chromatography
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;tandem mass spectrometry, or LC/MSMS. ZYN001, THC, and metabolites of THC (hydroxy
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;THC, or THC
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;OH, and 11
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;nor
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;delta
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;THC carboxylic acid, or TCH
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;COOH), were measured. No skin irritation or erythema was shown. Results of this study are reflected in Figure&nbsp;4 below.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Figure&nbsp;4. Plasma concentration vs time in guinea pig after ZYN001 patch application.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2016/03/14/0001558370-16-004082_ZYNC20151231X10K004.JPG" STYLE="WIDTH: 5.118055IN; HEIGHT: 2.5625IN" ALT="PICTURE 3">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ZYN001 achieved a steady
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;state plasma concentration of total THC equivalents of 6.90 &#xB1; 1.47 ng/mL. These results demonstrate that ZYN001 was rapidly converted to THC and sustained, consistent plasma levels of THC were achieved.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Clinical Trials
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The standard battery of genotoxicology studies required by the FDA for ZYN001 showed no adverse effects. The safety pharmacology studies required by the FDA demonstrated that ZYN001 has a pharmacology profile consistent with THC. The compound is currently being investigated in preclinical toxicology. We discussed our planned preclinical studies and clinical trials for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

	12

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#0563C1;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#ZYNC-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#0563C1;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>

</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ZYN001 with the FDA at a Pre
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;IND meeting in August&nbsp;2013. We anticipate initiating Phase&nbsp;1 clinical trials beginning in the second half of 2016. Phase&nbsp;2 clinical trials investigating ZYN001 in each individual indication are planned to begin in the first half of 2017.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Phase&nbsp;1 Clinical Trials&#x2014;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We plan to evaluate the tolerability and PK profile of ZYN001 in a Phase&nbsp;1 single rising dose clinical trial in healthy human subjects. Subsequent to the single rising dose clinical trial, we intend to conduct a Phase&nbsp;1 multiple rising dose clinical trials to examine the tolerability, PK and PD of multiple doses of ZYN001 in healthy human subjects and in patients with fibromyalgia. To complete the Phase&nbsp;1 program, we will conduct a bioequivalence clinical trial assessing the PK of ZYN001 when applied to various parts of the body (e.g.,&nbsp;arm, thigh and back).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;

<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="WIDTH:02.36%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #CCEEFF;PADDING:0PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="WIDTH:16.66%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #CCEEFF;PADDING:0PT;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0.05PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

	Patients who meet the American College of Rheumatology criteria for fibromyalgia syndrome

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#x2014; &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Depending on the results of Phase&nbsp;2a clinical trials, we may need to further define the dosing in Phase&nbsp;2b clinical trials or we may proceed directly into Phase&nbsp;3 clinical trials.
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
